A doctor walks in the Respiratory & Meningeal Pathogens Research Unit (RMPRU) at Chris Hani Baragwanath Hospital in Soweto. JOHANNESBURG - The total number of confirmed coronavirus related deaths in South Africa is 15,086. The Health Department has reported 82 new deaths in the last 24 hours. The majority of the deaths are from KwaZulu Natal (27), Western Cape (20) and Gauteng (15). The Eastern Cape (9), Free State (6) and Northern Cape (5) have also reported fatalities. There have been 1,079 new COVID-19 cases in the last 24 hours. READ: SA daily COVID-19 cases drop below 1,000, lowest in months This brings the total number of accumulated cases to 640, 441. The recovery rate stands at 88.6-percent which means 567, 729 people have recovered from the virus. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.